    <note>Liu(2) Ruoxu [11547] His education began with works on document models such as Bo(1) Juyi's (not in dataset) Boshi liudie, followed by the study of the five classics. He was very filial and when a parent was ill, he did not drink wine or eat meat and even of the weather were very hot, he wore strict clothing. Ding(1) Wei [1641] heard his name and wanted to meet with him, but Ruoxu did not go. (Ruoxu's #2 son, Yi(4) [11557], once remarked to Cai(1) Xiang [1651] that when Ding(1) Wei treated the world as his private domain (si tianxia), that all shi should have retired. Cai Xiang, WJ, 37.14b-18a. CBD, 5, 3968.</note>
